<item>
            <title>[HBASE-10577] Remove unnecessary looping in FSHLog</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10577</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the new disruptor based FSHLog, the Syncer threads are handed a batch of SyncFuture objects from the RingBufferHandler. The Syncer then invokes a sync call on the current writer instance.&lt;br/&gt;
This handing of batch is done in serially in RingBufferHandler, that is, every syncer receives a non overlapping batch of SyncFutures. Once synced, Syncer thread updates highestSyncedSequence.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the run method of Syncer, we have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; currentHighestSyncedSequence = highestSyncedSequence.get();
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (currentSequence &amp;lt; currentHighestSyncedSequence) {
              syncCount += releaseSyncFuture(takeSyncFuture, currentHighestSyncedSequence, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;);
              &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Done with the &apos;take&apos;.  Go around again and &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; a &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &apos;take&apos;.
&lt;/span&gt;              &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;continue&lt;/span&gt;;
            }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I find this logic of polling the BlockingQueue again in this condition un-necessary. When the currentHighestSyncedSequence is already greater than currentSequence, then doesn&apos;t it mean some other Syncer has already synced SyncFuture of these ops ? And, we should just go ahead and release all the SyncFutures for this batch to unblock the handlers. That would avoid polling the Blockingqueue for all SyncFuture objects in this case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
